Governors elected on the platform of the APC have resolved to work with their counterparts of the opposition PDP and the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) to tackle the security challenges bedevilling the nation.  Governor of Kebbi State and Chairman of the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF), Atiku Bagudu, in a statement on Sunday titled ‘Rescue of Abducted GSSS Kankara Students’, said the rescue attested to the capacity and competence of Nigerian security agencies to protect, defend and secure the country.  Governors elected on the platform of the APC have resolved to work with their counterparts of the opposition PDP and the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) to tackle the security challenges bedevilling the nation.  Governor of Kebbi State and Chairman of the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF), Atiku Bagudu, in a statement on Sunday titled ‘Rescue of Abducted GSSS Kankara Students’, said the rescue attested to the capacity and competence of Nigerian security agencies to protect, defend and secure the country. 